`output/tex_runtime_real_capture_attempt/`: en 640x480x16 la session sort en
`exited_1`, imprime `MMX.......Detected`, puis echoue cote pixel-format
D3D/display mode sans produire les trois artefacts de capture. Une variante
isolee `renderer=no3d` dans
`output/tex_runtime_real_capture_attempt_no3d/` garde le processus vivant
jusqu'au timeout controle (`started_timeout`, `timed_out=1`), mais ne produit
toujours aucun fichier dans `captures/`; le verrou restant est donc l'injection
ou l'activation du hook/logger TE. Une trace `winedbg` bornee est aussi
consignee dans `output/lolg95_winedbg_payload_trace_attempt/`, avec une variante
`no3d` dans `output/lolg95_winedbg_payload_trace_attempt_no3d/`: les 7
breakpoints payload-offset sont acceptes par `winedbg`, mais aucun n'est touche
en 90s sans pilotage de gameplay ni hook natif. Les notes detaillees sont dans
`MISE_AU_POINT_PROJET.md` et `HD_TEXTURES.md`.

DOSBox Staging
==============

Welcome to DOSBox Staging, a modern continuation of the DOSBox project that focuses on ease of use, advanced features, and current development practices.

This package contains a development branch named refs/tags/v0.81.0 with commit 07f31ea7f of the DOSBox Staging project.

DOSBox Staging is meant as a (mostly) drop-in replacement for older DOSBox versions -- your existing configurations will continue to work, but you will have access to many advanced features.

To learn more, check out the Getting Started guide on our website:
https://dosbox-staging.github.io/getting-started/introduction/

Our project website:
https://dosbox-staging.github.io/

You can report bugs and ask questions in our GitHub repository:
https://github.com/dosbox-staging/dosbox-staging

If you want to chat, you will find fellow users and developers in the #dosbox-staging channel of Luxtorpeda project's Discord server:
https://discord.gg/WwAg3Xf

Have fun!

--The DOSBox Staging team
